caption: Love this place near Pantheon. Spending my weekend time sitting here enjoying coffee with friends, not far away is old cathedral and an antique open air market. There is a special store which I love a lot selling luxury secondhand products as LV and Hermes, not far from that is a store that sells small and mini parfum which I bought for decoration
Very pleasant atmosphere. Nice market.
Excellent place to people watch and soak in Paris with a glass of French wine.
sunbathing, a breath of fresh air.  highly recommended for children

It is a nice little garden with lots of benches and sitting space to have the afternoon lunch. There is hardly an unoccupied bench during lunch hours. It overlooks a fountain and has a small kids space as well. There is a gate facing the rue Mouffetard, and you can just walk towards it or may be the other street, rue Censier. I enjoy having my lunches there, when the weather is nice outside.
Fantastic autumn evening great food

Lovely little park in Paris 5 next to the church. Good place to sit and hear the birds and be with nature whilst eating a delicious pastry from one of the nearby patisseries - I really love the royal from Fournil de Mouffetard and the Tarte tartin from David Doualan which are 3min walk away. Of course, also close to the famous Carl Marletti patisserie across the road. Nice little playground for young children.
Great place for coffees
Small, quiet space to chill and eat lunch on a sunny day

It's a modest square next to a simple church but it represents the most authentic part of Parisian life. It is an integral part of a unique neighbourhood. No Royal palace or napoleonic statues, just real life people.

Very cute square with coffee shops and bars right by the church. Nice market and bookstore too.
